<L>__{interior delmonico's steak house, new orleans night, 1945}
<A>__{the bar and restaurant crowded with men, many with various kinds of handicaps from the war, drinking away their demons... and we see benjamin and thomas sitting at a table... thick steaks, baked potatoes, drinks at their elbows...}
<C>__{benjamin}
<D>__{you're still drinking sazerac with whiskey instead of brandy.}
<C>__{thomas button}
<D>__{i'm a man of habit.}
<C>__{benjamin}
<P>__{(smiles)}
<D>__{are you still visiting the house on bourbon street?}
<C>__{thomas button}
<P>__{(smiles)}
<D>__{not for a long time.}
<C>__{benjamin button's }
<D>__{i told him about my life... about my time at war... and he told me how he had devoted his business to making buttons for the war effort...}
<C>__{thomas button}
<D>__{the war has been kind to the button industry... we had gone from making forty thousand buttons a day to making two hundred and fifty thousand... we employed ten times the number of workers... we were operating around the clock...}
<A>__{and he quiets... the sound of the busy restaurant... and after some moments thomas tells him...}
<C>__{thomas button }
<D>__{i don't know how much longer i have to live...}
<C>__{benjamin}
<D>__{i'm sorry to hear that, mr. button.}
<A>__{and it seems like he is about to tell benjamin the entire truth... but he can't bring himself and instead...}
<C>__{thomas button}
<D>__{i don't have any people. i keep to myself. i i'm frightened. i hope you won't mind... but whenever it's possible... i would enjoy your company...}
<C>__{benjamin}
<D>__{i will do what i can, mr. button.}
<A>__{they quietly eat.}
<C>__{thomas button}
<P>__{(after a beat)}
<D>__{tell me benjamin, do you know anything about buttons?}
<C>__{benjamin}
<D>__{just what holds my shirt on.}
